  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "l7882qw3kqbQGOp0RxdMi0gPVe0=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:46.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# SwarmChannel Is Transport Only\n\nThe SwarmChannel abstraction is deliberately thin. It does not interpret operation semantics or resolve conflicts.\n\n## What SwarmChannel does\n\n- Uploads `SyncEnvelope` payloads to `/bytes`\n- Appends feed index pointers to the outbox feed\n- Polls peer feeds for new entries\n- Downloads referenced `/bytes` payloads into the inbox\n- Routes undeliverable or malformed messages to a deadLetter queue\n\n## What SwarmChannel does NOT do\n\n- Determine final operation order\n- Merge conflicting edits\n- Deduplicate operations\n- Compute document state\n\nAll of those responsibilities stay with the reactor's existing `SyncManager` and document model reducer \u2014 the same components that already handle sync in other transports (GraphQL, local storage, etc.).\n\n## Why this matters\n\nBecause ordering/conflict/dedup logic lives in the reactor, adding Swarm as a transport does not require bespoke merge code. Any channel that can move `SyncEnvelope` data satisfies the contract.\n",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:46.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:46.000Z"
    }
  },
